06:32.827 --> 06:34.325
Last night.

06:34.327 --> 06:36.161
Oh hey, check it out.

06:36.163 --> 06:37.199
Hot water.

06:38.166 --> 06:39.632
Look.

06:39.634 --> 06:41.933
Whoo, I told you it would work.

06:41.935 --> 06:44.936
Heated by some clever ingenuity
and a little mother nature.

06:44.938 --> 06:46.474
Next rainfall, we're set.

06:52.747 --> 06:54.116
Look what else I found.

06:54.949 --> 06:56.649
Batteries

06:56.651 --> 06:57.582
What for?

06:57.584 --> 06:59.318
I don't know, anything.

06:59.320 --> 07:01.387
I got them when
they were on sale.

07:01.389 --> 07:02.555
What size are they?

07:02.557 --> 07:04.455
Nine volt.

07:04.457 --> 07:05.327
Oh, man.

07:07.195 --> 07:09.227
Ugh, they're all expired

07:09.229 --> 07:13.267
Jesus Christ, play
some music for a change.

07:14.202 --> 07:15.269
It's okay, baby

07:18.438 --> 07:20.339
Honey, I'm sorry.

07:20.341 --> 07:22.440
There's no coffee
and I'm developing

07:22.442 --> 07:25.945
an intense hatred of oranges.

07:25.947 --> 07:26.911
We have figs.

07:26.913 --> 07:28.880
Yeah, and beans, Guy.

07:28.882 --> 07:31.349
Cans of beans.

07:31.351 --> 07:32.450
We also have those dried ones.

07:32.452 --> 07:36.357
What are they, the, lima
or navy bean or whatever?

07:37.925 --> 07:40.693
Look, I failed legume
identification class,

07:40.695 --> 07:43.764
but I think I can get a garden
going in that front room.

07:44.899 --> 07:47.265
You know, put some
dirt and those boxes,

07:47.267 --> 07:49.335
and there's easily enough light
out there to get one going.

07:49.337 --> 07:50.835
Yeah, if we can last
through tomato season,

07:50.837 --> 07:53.339
you're gonna have to shoot me,

07:53.341 --> 07:55.407
and please, can
you wear clothes?

07:55.409 --> 07:56.474
It doesn't matter anymore.

07:56.476 --> 07:57.476
Yes, it does.

07:57.478 --> 08:00.649
Just, at least wear pants, okay?

08:05.385 --> 08:06.585
Hey, look, see?

08:06.587 --> 08:07.685
I checked the fence.

08:07.687 --> 08:09.421
Okay, it's all good.

08:09.423 --> 08:10.923
It's fine.

08:10.925 --> 08:13.424
Choppers are still
buzzing around.

08:13.426 --> 08:14.359
I think one saw me this morning.

08:14.361 --> 08:15.394
Wait, what?

08:15.396 --> 08:16.428
Yeah.

08:16.430 --> 08:17.363
Why didn't you wake me up?

08:17.365 --> 08:18.563
Did you do a signal?

08:18.565 --> 08:20.431
Yes, I waived the
flag like crazy,

08:20.433 --> 08:22.835
but they just, they
weren't close enough.

08:22.837 --> 08:24.969
Next time, please wake me up.

08:24.971 --> 08:26.474
They'll be back, okay?

08:27.608 --> 08:28.944
I was just out there, and...

08:31.278 --> 08:32.346
What?

08:35.416 --> 08:36.284
Guy, what?

08:37.784 --> 08:38.751
Maria turned.

08:43.623 --> 08:45.591
Paige, oh, goddammit.

08:45.593 --> 08:46.428
Come on.

08:52.400 --> 08:53.001
Paige.

08:55.435 --> 08:56.735
Maria?

08:56.737 --> 08:57.872
Paige.

09:00.541 --> 09:01.709
That's my bracelet.

09:02.943 --> 09:04.246
I let her borrow it.

09:09.617 --> 09:10.481
Paige, come on.

09:10.483 --> 09:11.619
Come on, baby.

09:14.754 --> 09:15.956
Nope, nope.

09:17.325 --> 09:18.425
It's not our fault.

09:19.627 --> 09:21.459
She should've been
in here, with us.

09:21.461 --> 09:22.363
They all should have.

09:23.531 --> 09:24.332
We tried.

09:26.467 --> 09:27.066
God, I hate this.

09:27.068 --> 09:28.033
Where are they?

09:28.035 --> 09:28.967
Why haven't they come yet?

09:28.969 --> 09:31.339
Isn't this exactly why we taxes?

09:33.406 --> 09:35.741
I think I'm gonna
take up painting.

09:35.743 --> 09:37.342
What do you think?

09:37.344 --> 09:38.409
Seriously?

09:38.411 --> 09:39.577
Yeah, why not?

09:39.579 --> 09:41.746
I mean, the air's getting
cleaner without all the traffic.

09:41.748 --> 09:44.015
Just sit out there and
just breathe it in.

09:44.017 --> 09:46.353
I'm getting so much
sleep, I feel great.

09:47.488 --> 09:49.454
I have all this creative energy.

09:49.456 --> 09:51.957
I feel fucking
creative, you know?

09:51.959 --> 09:53.328
I love my knife wall.

09:54.762 --> 09:57.596
Is this how you spent
your days, just waking up

09:57.598 --> 09:59.800
and I don't know, making shit?

10:01.001 --> 10:02.433
Are you okay if I use
your paints and stuff?

10:02.435 --> 10:03.872
I promise, I'll do
my chores first.

10:06.474 --> 10:07.541
Thank you, honey

12:46.599 --> 12:47.734
Hello?

17:38.458 --> 17:39.291
Hey, Guy?

17:39.293 --> 17:40.128
Mmm.

17:43.330 --> 17:44.132
What are these?

17:45.065 --> 17:46.133
I was cleaning out your desk.

17:49.503 --> 17:50.338
All right.

17:51.604 --> 17:53.071
- Done.
- What are you doing?

17:53.073 --> 17:54.272
I wanted to talk
to you about that.

17:54.274 --> 17:55.877
It doesn't matter anymore.

17:58.411 --> 18:00.411
Do you think he's
alone in there?

18:00.413 --> 18:02.013
He always was before.

18:02.015 --> 18:04.181
Hey, we could snag
his plant collection.

18:04.183 --> 18:06.351
No, Guy, you're not
going in after his weed.

18:06.353 --> 18:07.486
That's stupid.

18:07.488 --> 18:10.892
Yeah, well, look, he's not
gonna get out, I promise.

18:13.459 --> 18:15.493
Well, I'm not sleeping
with him out there.

18:15.495 --> 18:16.330
I can't.

18:18.598 --> 18:19.399
Come on.

18:20.267 --> 18:21.401
Trust me.

18:24.071 --> 18:25.238
Don't you fuck this up.

18:28.609 --> 18:29.477
Shut up.

18:31.612 --> 18:32.846
What a jerk.

18:43.323 --> 18:46.291
Guy, I found
my other phone charger.

18:46.293 --> 18:48.059
If there's no internet,

18:48.061 --> 18:49.593
I seriously doubt they're
worried about cell towers.

18:49.595 --> 18:52.063
Yeah, well, I'm gonna
keep trying to do the,

18:52.065 --> 18:53.234
what're you doing?

18:55.067 --> 18:57.337
I'm deciding on what kind
of painter I want to be.

19:00.274 --> 19:01.672
What, my chores are done.

19:01.674 --> 19:02.940
Guy!

19:02.942 --> 19:03.577
They are!

19:17.090 --> 19:17.925
Guy, hey.

19:19.492 --> 19:21.993
Oh, I like it, honey.

19:21.995 --> 19:23.264
Ordered chaos.

19:24.331 --> 19:25.530
But you know what?

19:25.532 --> 19:26.363
I think if I'm gonna
start with still life,

19:26.365 --> 19:27.998
I think I want nature.

19:28.000 --> 19:28.800
You know, like the back yard

19:28.802 --> 19:31.236
is some kind of
like a modern Eden.

19:31.238 --> 19:33.338
Oh my God, you found
my Kurosawa sword.

19:33.340 --> 19:34.272
No, Guy, stop it.

19:34.274 --> 19:35.940
This is not a still life.

19:35.942 --> 19:38.043
We're into week three and
everything you see here,

19:38.045 --> 19:40.210
this is all we have
left in the house.

19:40.212 --> 19:43.047
No, we have
oranges, we have figs,

19:43.049 --> 19:44.949
we have plenty of water.

19:44.951 --> 19:47.151
Look, you didn't even
comment on my invention.

19:47.153 --> 19:49.053
We're gonna have
rainwater from the roof.

19:49.055 --> 19:51.255
We live in a desert.

19:51.257 --> 19:52.489
You know what?

19:52.491 --> 19:53.658
I've tasted your life
for a few days now.

19:53.660 --> 19:56.127
The no worries, no hassles,

19:56.129 --> 19:57.361
doing exactly doing
what you want to do,

19:57.363 --> 19:59.965
and I don't want to give it up
now, not if I don't have to.

19:59.967 --> 20:01.967
You think that I
sat around all day

20:01.969 --> 20:04.335
and just played
paint by numbers?

20:04.337 --> 20:07.037
No, Guy, there were phone
calls that I had to make

20:07.039 --> 20:10.274
and galleries I had to
pitch and a bunch of essays

20:10.276 --> 20:14.044
I had to write about why
I do blah blah bullshit

20:14.046 --> 20:15.447
as a contemporary painter.

20:15.449 --> 20:17.114
And for every single
person that said yes to me,

20:17.116 --> 20:19.484
50 said no, 100
people said no to me.

20:19.486 --> 20:21.119
That was my life
every single day,

20:21.121 --> 20:22.419
just a bunch of fucking
people saying no.

20:22.421 --> 20:25.156
Okay, so you want
to go back to that?

20:25.158 --> 20:26.026
No.

20:27.160 --> 20:28.293
Yes, I do.

20:28.295 --> 20:30.461
Maybe.

20:33.100 --> 20:35.467
Okay, and what about Mark, huh?

20:35.469 --> 20:37.736
He's not getting out.

20:40.239 --> 20:41.072
Do you hear that?

20:41.074 --> 20:43.240
See, see?

20:43.242 --> 20:44.044
Paige.

21:00.794 --> 21:02.159
See us!

21:02.161 --> 21:03.064
Fuck, see us!

21:04.131 --> 21:04.732
See us.

21:28.622 --> 21:29.489
Honey!

21:37.096 --> 21:38.362
Jesus.

21:38.364 --> 21:39.200
Honey!

21:46.305 --> 21:48.275
I'm not gonna sleep
with him like that.

21:49.375 --> 21:50.744
What do you want me to do?

21:51.678 --> 21:53.113
That's my Kurosawa sword.

21:54.213 --> 21:56.413
This is about survival.

21:56.415 --> 21:58.149
No, that's mine and you
shouldn't be touching it.

21:58.151 --> 21:59.583
Guy, eventually there's
gonna be so many of them

21:59.585 --> 22:00.752
that we're not
gonna keep them out.

22:00.754 --> 22:02.653
You're gonna kill my friend

22:02.655 --> 22:04.688
with my limited
edition Kurosawa sword?

22:04.690 --> 22:05.526
Yes!

22:08.260 --> 22:09.761
No, you're gonna do it.

22:09.763 --> 22:11.161
Oh, I am?

22:11.163 --> 22:11.862
Yeah!

22:11.864 --> 22:12.863
Oh, okay, and why my friend?

22:12.865 --> 22:14.134
Why not yours?

22:15.267 --> 22:16.234
Guy?

22:16.236 --> 22:17.669
No, why not?

22:17.671 --> 22:19.169
Guy, wait.

22:19.171 --> 22:20.170
Oh no, but this
is about survival.

22:20.172 --> 22:21.639
No, just wait.

22:21.641 --> 22:23.408
What, just because he's
dead, it doesn't matter?

22:23.410 --> 22:24.742
Come on, stop!

22:24.744 --> 22:26.244
Do it.

22:26.246 --> 22:27.748
Since it's so easy,
I want to see this.

22:39.860 --> 22:43.064
You have to cut off her
head, or at least smash it.

22:47.234 --> 22:49.303
Go, smash Maria's brains.

23:14.693 --> 23:16.229
Okay, yes, I get it.

23:21.234 --> 23:22.670
This shit's not even sharp.

23:36.382 --> 23:37.181
Don't cry, baby.

23:37.183 --> 23:38.251
I'm not crying.

23:38.951 --> 23:39.752
I just, shit.

23:42.354 --> 23:43.388
Guy, I don't feel anything.

23:43.390 --> 23:45.258
It's like we're already dead.

23:46.426 --> 23:47.060
Are you kidding?

23:48.562 --> 23:50.594
A month ago I was killing myself

23:50.596 --> 23:53.898
trying to keep this house,
trying to keep us afloat.

23:53.900 --> 23:54.701
I know.

23:55.901 --> 23:58.139
There's no stress here.

23:59.538 --> 24:01.973
I mean, there's no
mortgage, you know?

24:01.975 --> 24:03.774
No bills.

24:03.776 --> 24:05.275
No deadlines.

24:05.277 --> 24:07.344
No getting up at fucking
5:30 in the morning

24:07.346 --> 24:09.746
for some bullshit
client meeting downtown,

24:09.748 --> 24:12.483
that I don't have to
be there for anyway.

24:12.485 --> 24:14.851
I mean, there's no debt.

24:14.853 --> 24:15.719
Gone.

24:15.721 --> 24:16.553
Student loans?

24:16.555 --> 24:17.391
Yeah, gone.

24:19.292 --> 24:21.458
And babe, think
about all the things

24:21.460 --> 24:24.228
that we've wanted to do, right?

24:24.230 --> 24:27.232
All the books that you've never
finished reading, you know?

24:27.234 --> 24:30.334
All the time, all the time.

24:30.336 --> 24:32.769
I mean, fuck, every
night, you telling me

24:32.771 --> 24:34.238
that you don't have enough
time to get things done.

24:34.240 --> 24:35.473
How many times
have you said that?

24:35.475 --> 24:36.608
All the time.

24:36.610 --> 24:39.280
All the time, all the time.

24:40.680 --> 24:44.381
This is the best thing that
could've ever happened.

24:44.383 --> 24:47.384
Okay, okay, look, I know, it's
not the most ideal scenario,

24:47.386 --> 24:48.486
but, you know?

24:50.723 --> 24:52.325
If it was gonna happen anyway...

24:55.327 --> 24:56.460
You know what?

24:56.462 --> 24:58.598
We've got plenty of food,
we've got plenty of water.

25:03.370 --> 25:04.268
Guy!

25:38.971 --> 25:40.373
You killed Bill.

25:43.442 --> 25:45.075
Yeah, well he blew
shit into our yard

25:45.077 --> 25:47.312
all the time and he knows it.

25:47.314 --> 25:47.948
Honey.

25:50.482 --> 25:52.082
I married you because
if anything like this

25:52.084 --> 25:55.722
was ever gonna happen, I
wanted it to happen with you,

25:58.691 --> 25:59.892
so let's not leave.

26:51.411 --> 26:52.442
Yes!

27:22.808 --> 27:24.478
And you wanted
to sell my DVDs.

27:31.049 --> 27:34.185
Ugh, no, no, no,
no, no, no, I can't.

27:34.187 --> 27:35.488
No more.

27:36.690 --> 27:41.461
Isn't there like a disease
that's the opposite of scurvy?

27:43.095 --> 27:47.130
Oh my God, I have
reverse scurvy.

27:47.132 --> 27:48.768
I know I have it.

27:49.869 --> 27:50.804
No.

27:52.572 --> 27:53.474
I think I do.

27:54.908 --> 27:56.677
I don't even know
what scurvy is.

27:58.210 --> 27:59.579
It's, like, a pirate thing.

28:10.222 --> 28:11.624
I'm still worried, you know?

28:12.758 --> 28:15.962
They'll let us
know when it's okay.

28:17.896 --> 28:18.830
We'll check every day.

28:18.832 --> 28:21.064
No, not just about that.

28:21.066 --> 28:24.968
You know how you said that
you have all this freedom now

28:24.970 --> 28:29.175
and all this time to just
do whatever we want and,

28:31.143 --> 28:32.512
I don't feel like painting.

28:33.246 --> 28:35.580
Like, not at all.

28:35.582 --> 28:36.617
Give it time.

28:37.249 --> 28:38.084
You will.

28:42.020 --> 28:44.524
You finished off that
whiskey, didn't you?

28:45.557 --> 28:46.559
Yeah, I'm sorry.

28:48.795 --> 28:51.161
It's funny, I always
thought that paradise

28:51.163 --> 28:53.533
would have an open bar.

28:59.271 --> 29:00.873
I've decided I'm a Manet.

29:02.709 --> 29:03.975
Not Monet, but Manet.

29:03.977 --> 29:06.043
Yeah, I know the difference.

29:06.045 --> 29:08.044
I'm just letting you know
that I know the difference.

29:08.046 --> 29:10.049
Miss smarty pants, MFA painter.

29:15.787 --> 29:18.525
Nobody decides what kind
of artist they're gonna be,

29:19.625 --> 29:20.594
they just paint.

